  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 15 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 5 critical, 15 high, 7 medium, 12 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 17 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, thunderstorm / convective risk and mist  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD). Network hotspots: Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Ålesund Airport, Vigra (AES/ENAL), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 10 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 9 others.",
